b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Adobe Firefly is best suited for commercial projects, designers, Adobe workflow, safe content, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Ideogram, meanwhile, shines for logos, typography, text in images, poster design, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Adobe Firefly describes itself as \"Adobe's commercially safe AI image generator trained on licensed content.\" Ideogram, established in 2023, positions itself as \"AI image generator excelling at text, logos, and typography.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Adobe Firefly** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Ideogram is a poor choice — far from it. Ideogram excels in its own right, particularly for logos and typography.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value trained on licensed content, safe for commercial use, go with Adobe Firefly. If excellent text rendering, especially for logos matters more to you, Ideogram is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
